    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- RANKED LIST -->
  <section class="problem-section" id="ranked-list">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">The full list</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">10 free social media tools for local business, <span class="accent">ranked by practical value and what the free plan actually covers.</span></h2>
      <p>Organized by function: scheduling, design, analytics, and management. Each entry includes exact free plan limits so you know what you're actually getting.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="service-1">
      <div class="ba-col after" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#1 · $49/MO AFTER $1 TRIAL · 30 POSTS/MONTH AUTOMATED</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">theStacc Social Media Module — Best for local businesses that want social media done without doing it</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">Not free — but ranked first because the time math is unambiguous for most local business owners.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Free tools save money. theStacc saves time. The Social Media module publishes 30 posts per month across Instagram, Facebook, LinkedIn, and X — written and scheduled automatically based on your business type, location, and brand voice. You connect your accounts, set a tone, and theStacc handles the rest. For a local business owner spending 5–10 hours per month managing social media manually, $49/month is a straightforward trade. Bundle with the Local SEO module ($49) for automatic Google Business Profile posting too.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✓</span>
            <div>
              <h4>30 posts/month published automatically — no manual writing or scheduling</h4>
              <p>Posts are written based on your business, industry, and location. Scheduled across platforms. Published automatically. You don't touch it — it just runs.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✓</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Bundle with Blog SEO and Local SEO for a complete content operation</h4>
              <p>Blog SEO ($99) + Social Media ($49) + Local SEO ($49) = $197/month for 30 blog articles, 30 social posts, and full GBP automation. Bundle and save 15%.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✓</span>
            <div>
              <h4>No consistency risk — posts publish whether you're busy or not</h4>
              <p>The #1 failure mode for local business social media is inconsistency. One busy week and posting stops. theStacc posts automatically — busy months don't interrupt the schedule.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✗</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Honest con: not free — and no creative control over individual posts</h4>
              <p>$49/month. Content is generated based on your business profile — you don't review or approve individual posts. If you need to control every caption, theStacc isn't the right fit.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <div style="margin-top: 24px;">
          <a href="/checkout/" class="btn btn-primary"><span>Start the $1 trial <span class="arrow">→</span></span></a>
          <a href="/modules/social-media/" class="btn btn-secondary" style="margin-left: 12px;">See Social Media module</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="service-2" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#2 · FREE · 3 CHANNELS · 10 POSTS/CHANNEL QUEUE</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Buffer — Best free scheduling tool for local businesses</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For solo business owners who want to batch-schedule a week of social content in one sitting — zero learning curve, zero cost.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Buffer is the easiest scheduling tool available. Connect your social accounts, write posts, pick times, and Buffer publishes automatically. The free plan covers 3 social channels and a queue of 10 posts per channel. No credit card required. No expiry date on the free tier. New users are publishing within 10 minutes of signing up. The narrowness of the free plan (no team features, no analytics depth, no content calendar view) is the only limitation for growing businesses.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Zero learning curve — live in 10 minutes</h4><p>The simplest scheduling interface available. If you can write a social media post, you can use Buffer. No training required.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Genuinely free — 3 channels, no credit card, no expiry</h4><p>Instagram, Facebook, and LinkedIn on the free tier covers the most important channels for most local businesses.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Queue-based scheduling — batch your week in one session</h4><p>Fill the queue on Monday. Buffer posts throughout the week automatically. Reduces daily social media time to near zero.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: 10 posts/channel queue empties fast</h4><p>Posting once per day means refilling the queue every 10 days. More than twice per day requires upgrading. Not a dealbreaker, but a recurring chore.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="service-3" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#3 · FREE · 1 BRAND · 7 CHANNELS · GBP INCLUDED</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Zoho Social — Best free tool that includes Google Business Profile scheduling</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For local businesses focused on local SEO that want to schedule Google Business Profile posts alongside social media — at no cost.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Zoho Social's free plan covers 1 brand across 7 channels — Facebook, Instagram, LinkedIn, X, TikTok, Pinterest, and Google Business Profile. Unlimited posts. A publishing calendar. GBP scheduling is the standout feature: most free tools don't support GBP, and Zoho Social does. For local businesses where GBP presence is more important than social media engagement, this is the single best free tool available.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Google Business Profile scheduling — rare in free social tools</h4><p>Most free schedulers support Instagram, Facebook, and LinkedIn. Almost none support GBP. Zoho Social does. For local search visibility, GBP posts matter more than any other channel.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Unlimited posts across 7 channels on the free plan</h4><p>No queue limit. No post cap. Schedule as much as you want on the free tier. More generous than Buffer's 10-post-per-channel limit.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Publishing calendar included</h4><p>Calendar view of scheduled posts. See the week or month at a glance. Identifies content gaps before they happen.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: 1 user only — no team collaboration on free</h4><p>The free plan is for solo operators. If two people manage your social media, you'll need to upgrade or share login credentials (not recommended).</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="service-4" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#4 · FREE · UNLIMITED POSTS · FACEBOOK + INSTAGRAM</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Meta Business Suite — Best free tool for Facebook and Instagram management</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For local businesses where Facebook and Instagram are the primary channels — unlimited posting, scheduling, and inbox management at no cost.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Meta Business Suite is Meta's own management platform for business Facebook and Instagram accounts. It's completely free, unlimited, and handles scheduling, posting, inbox management (combined DMs and comments from both platforms), basic analytics, and ad management. If Facebook and Instagram are your primary social channels, this is the only tool you need. The limitation: Meta only. No cross-platform scheduling for LinkedIn, X, or TikTok.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Completely free — unlimited posts, scheduling, and inbox management</h4><p>No post limits, no queue caps, no paid tiers required for core features. The most capable free tool for Facebook and Instagram management.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Unified inbox for Facebook and Instagram messages and comments</h4><p>All DMs and comments from both platforms in one feed. Faster response times. No missed customer messages across two separate apps.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Insights and ad management included</h4><p>Post performance data and boosting tools directly in the same platform. No external analytics tool needed for Facebook and Instagram specifically.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: Meta-only — no LinkedIn, X, TikTok, or GBP</h4><p>If you're active on channels beyond Facebook and Instagram, you need a separate tool. Meta Business Suite has no plans to support non-Meta platforms.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="service-5" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#5 · FREE · UNLIMITED POSTS · LOCAL SEARCH VISIBILITY</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Google Business Profile — Most important free local social platform</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For every local business. GBP posts influence local search rankings directly — this is not optional, it's foundational.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Google Business Profile is not typically classified as a "social media tool" — but it functions as one, and it's the most important social platform for local search visibility. GBP posts, offers, events, and Q&A content all influence your local Map Pack ranking. A business posting to GBP weekly sees measurably better local rankings than a business that doesn't. The profile is completely free. Posting is free. The only cost is time — which theStacc's Local SEO module eliminates for $49/month.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Direct local search ranking influence — no other social platform does this</h4><p>Instagram posts don't affect Google rankings. GBP posts do. For any local business trying to rank in Maps, active GBP posting is the highest-ROI social activity available.</p></div></li>
